            "creation_date": 1410504123,
            "body": "<p>Simply create the <code>Locale<\/code> object with the desired language and country code, for example:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Locale finnish = new Locale(\"fi\", \"FI\");\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>You're not restricted to the constants that are defined in the <code>Locale<\/code> class.<\/p>\n\n<p>See the <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/Locale.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">API documentation<\/a>.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 25802279,
            "question_id": 25802158
        },
